      "content": "That is a very dangerous assumption, and you are absolutely right to be wary of taking a \"small dose\" without medical supervision. St. John's Wort is not a benign herbal remedy; it interacts with sertraline in a way that can lead to severe serotonin toxicity, which can cause seizures, high blood pressure, and even death. Because of this risk, you should not try to test a dose yourself, and you have every right to insist on speaking with your doctor about your options.",
